As shown in the figure below, a circular park consists of an outer-ring path for walkers and a ring-shaped flower garden surrounding a central circular fountain. The walking path is six feet wide in all places, the garden ring is eight feet wide in all places, and the fountain has a diameter of 10 feet. 

\begin{center}
\begin{asy}
size(5cm);
draw(circle((0,0),19));
draw(circle((0,0),13));
draw(circle((0,0),5));
draw("$8'$",(0,5)--(0,13));
draw("$6'$",(13,0)--(19,0));
\end{asy}
\end{center}
What is the diameter, in feet, of the circle that is the outer boundary of the walking path? (Source: AoPS)
}

\textbf{Answer:} The diameter is $10 + 2\cdot 6 + 2\cdot 8$ or $\boxed{38}$ feet.
}
